<item>
<title><![CDATA[Building a Digital Strategy That Lasts]]></title>
<link>https://example.com/?p=101</link>
<pubDate>Mon, 12 Jan 2026 09:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
<guid isPermaLink="false">https://example.com/?p=101</guid>
<description></description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Too many digital strategies are really just a list of tactics in disguise. A new website here, a campaign there, a tool everyone forgets to use. A strategy that lasts starts with a clear answer to one question: what are we actually trying to change?</p>

<h2>Begin with outcomes, not channels</h2>
<p>Before debating platforms or budgets, we help clients define the business outcomes that matter, the customer behaviours that drive them, and the few metrics worth watching. Everything else follows from there.</p>

<h2>Build for the next three years</h2>
<p>Technology and channels will change, but your customers' underlying needs move far more slowly. A durable strategy invests in the things that compound, your data, your brand, and your team's capability, instead of chasing every new platform.</p>

<p>The result is a roadmap your whole organisation can rally behind, one that still makes sense long after the launch buzz has faded.</p>]]></content:encoded>
<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[A strategy that lasts starts with a clear answer to one question: what are we actually trying to change?]]></excerpt:encoded>
