<item>
<title><![CDATA[Five Signs It's Time to Rebrand]]></title>
<link>https://example.com/?p=104</link>
<pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 09:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
<guid isPermaLink="false">https://example.com/?p=104</guid>
<description></description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>A rebrand is a big undertaking, so it should never be done on a whim. But there are moments when keeping the old identity quietly holds a business back. Here are the signals we watch for.</p>

<h2>The brand no longer matches the business</h2>
<p>You have outgrown your original story. The products, the audience, or the ambition have moved on, but the logo and messaging are still describing the company you used to be.</p>

<h2>You are embarrassed to share your own website</h2>
<p>If the team hesitates before sending a link to a prospect, that is data. Pride in your brand is a competitive advantage, and the lack of it shows.</p>

<p>Other signs include inconsistent visuals across channels, a name that no longer fits, and a market that has shifted around you. One sign is worth watching. Three or more, and it is time to talk.</p>]]></content:encoded>
<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[There are moments when keeping the old identity quietly holds a business back. Here are the signals we watch for.]]></excerpt:encoded>
